        "Act cheerful and optimistic regardless of how they feel": "This is the OPPOSITE of genuineness. Acting cheerful when feeling concerned would be incongruent—internal feelings not matching external behavior. Genuineness means if the therapist feels concerned, they show concern; if they feel warmth, they show warmth. Putting on an act (always cheerful) creates a facade, which Rogers specifically argued against."
